#compdef flowgger
# =============================================================================
# flowgger — Frank Denis + AWS Labs's "fast, simple and
#          lightweight data collector" — a Rust-native
#          syslog + structured-log ingestion daemon that
#          accepts log records over stdin / UDP / TCP /
#          TLS / Redis-list / file-tail sources, parses
#          them via pluggable decoders (RFC5424, RFC3164,
#          GELF JSON, LTSV, Cap'n Proto, passthrough),
#          and re-emits them via pluggable encoders to
#          Apache Kafka, NATS, downstream-Flowgger,
#          stdout, or Graylog.  Designed as a Rust
#          alternative to Logstash + Fluentd that
#          dispenses with the JVM + Ruby runtime
#          dependencies + is orders of magnitude faster
#          on log-throughput benchmarks.
#          Distinguishing from Logstash (Elastic's
#          JRuby-on-JVM log pipeline; heavyweight, slow
#          startup), Fluentd (Treasure Data's Ruby-on-
#          CRuby log forwarder; also heavyweight),
#          Vector (DataDog's Rust observability data
#          router; broader scope including metrics +
#          traces), syslog-ng (older C-implemented
#          syslog daemon; less flexible encoding),
#          rsyslog (RHEL's syslog daemon; basic), and
#          Filebeat / Elastic Beats (Go-based shippers
#          tied to Elastic stack) by:
#            - REDIS-RS FOUNDATION — uses redis-rs/
#              redis as a DIRECT dependency in
#              Cargo.toml (this is the headline CLI
#              library that OPENS Axis 45 on the Rust
#              side AND marks the **100-LIBRARY-PER-
#              LANGUAGE LANDMARK** on the Rust side;
#              see taxonomy notes below) for the
#              `redis-input` feature: Flowgger
#              subscribes to Redis lists or pub/sub
#              channels and processes incoming
#              records as if they arrived via syslog,
#              enabling Redis-as-message-queue
#              deployment topologies
#            - PARANOID PARSING — Frank Denis's
#              design philosophy: aggressive input
#              validation to PREVENT injection of
#              malformed/incomplete records down the
#              chain.  Logstash + Fluentd's loose
#              parsing has historically allowed
#              attackers to inject control records;
#              Flowgger's RFC5424 implementation
#              treats spec deviation as a hard reject
#            - NO UNSAFE CODE — `#![forbid(unsafe_code)]`
#              throughout the Flowgger codebase; the
#              entire data pipeline operates in safe
#              Rust.  No CGo, no C linkage beyond the
#              optional openssl crate for TLS
#            - SINGLE-EXECUTABLE DEPLOYMENT —
#              `flowgger` is a single statically-
#              linked binary; no JVM, no Ruby
#              interpreter, no shared-library
#              dependencies beyond optional openssl.
#              Drop on a server + run; ideal for
#              air-gapped + minimal-image deployments
#            - INPUT PLUGINS — pluggable via feature
#              flags + flowgger.toml configuration:
#              * stdin
#              * UDP (RFC5426-style)
#              * TCP
#              * TLS (RFC5425)
#              * Redis (list pop or pub/sub via the
#                `redis` crate)
#              * file (tail via the `notify` crate)
#            - DECODER PLUGINS:
#              * RFC5424 (modern syslog with
#                structured data)
#              * RFC3164 (legacy syslog)
#              * GELF JSON (Graylog Extended Log
#                Format)
#              * LTSV (Labeled Tab-Separated Values)
#              * Cap'n Proto (binary structured
#                schema)
#              * passthrough (no parsing; pass raw
#                bytes)
#            - ENCODER + OUTPUT PLUGINS:
#              * Kafka producer (gzip/snappy
#                compression via the `kafka` crate)
#              * NATS (via async-nats)
#              * downstream-Flowgger (chain multiple
#                Flowgger instances)
#              * stdout
#              * Graylog
#              * Cap'n Proto re-encoding
#              * GELF re-encoding
#            - TLS via OPENSSL — optional `tls`
#              feature pulls in the openssl crate for
#              TLS-encrypted TCP input + TLS Kafka
#              connections; defaults to system
#              OpenSSL trust store
#            - COROUTINE-BASED CONCURRENCY (optional)
#              — the `coroutines` feature flag pulls
#              in the may stackful-coroutine library
#              for high-fanout deployments where
#              tokio's task overhead becomes
#              measurable; alternative path to
#              tokio-task concurrency
#            - DEFAULT FEATURE SET — `default = [
#              "syslog", "kafka-output", "file",
#              "redis", "capnp-recompile", "tls",
#              "gelf", "ltsv"]` — opinionated bundle
#              that supports most production
#              deployments out of the box; users with
#              tighter binary-size budgets can build
#              with `--no-default-features` + select
#              subset
#            - TOML CONFIGURATION — `flowgger.toml`
#              (default) declares input + decoder +
#              encoder + output pipelines with type-
#              checked TOML parsing; the entire
#              behavior is declarative, not coded;
#              operators can iterate the
#              configuration without rebuilding the
#              binary
#            - HOT-RELOAD via file watching — file-
#              based inputs use the `notify` crate
#              for filesystem watching; rotated logs
#              are automatically re-opened without
#              manual intervention
#            - 883+ STARS ON awslabs/flowgger —
#              backed by AWS Labs as the corporate
#              sponsor (originally developed at AWS
#              before being open-sourced); active
#              maintenance + ISC license + multi-
#              maintainer (Frank Denis + Matteo
#              Bigoi + Vivien Chene + Francesco
#              Berni)
#          Used by: large-scale syslog ingestion
#          deployments (AWS-internal + external),
#          security-conscious environments that need
#          paranoid input validation as a first line
#          of defense, organizations migrating off
#          Logstash + Fluentd to reduce JVM/Ruby
#          operational overhead, and log-pipeline
#          designers building Kafka-fronted
#          observability stacks.
#
# Author:  Frank Denis (jedisct1 on GitHub;
#          https://00f.net; based in Antibes,
#          France) as primary author + maintainer;
#          co-authors Matteo Bigoi (bigo@crisidev.org),
#          Vivien Chene (viv.chene@gmail.com),
#          Francesco Berni (kurojishi@kurojishi.me).
#          Frank Denis is also the author of:
#            - dnscrypt-proxy (encrypted DNS
#              resolver)
#            - libsodium (modern cryptographic
#              library; powers Signal, WireGuard,
#              etc.)
#            - sandbox2 (sandboxing primitives)
#            - mini-sign (signature verification)
#            - many other influential crypto + Rust
#              + C systems projects
#          Sponsorship: AWS Labs (the awslabs/
#          flowgger repository).
# Source:  https://github.com/awslabs/flowgger
#          https://github.com/awslabs/flowgger/blob/master/src/main.rs
#          https://github.com/awslabs/flowgger/blob/master/Cargo.toml
# Manpage: No traditional manpage; `flowgger --help`
#          shows clap-derived help (very minimal —
#          one optional config file argument);
#          full documentation in repo wiki at
#          https://github.com/awslabs/flowgger/wiki +
#          extensive flowgger.toml examples
# Library: redis-rs/redis (Armin Ronacher's "Redis
#          library for Rust").  This is the headline
#          dependency for this completion's axis-45
#          opening role; see taxonomy notes below.
#          Also clap v4 (Axis 1 argparse), log v0.4
#          (Axis 9 logging), rand v0.8, flate2 v1
#          (gzip/deflate via miniz_oxide), notify
#          v4 (file watching, optional), openssl
#          ~0.10 (TLS, optional), kafka v0.8
#          (snappy + gzip + security features,
#          optional), async-nats v0.42 (optional),
#          capnp v0.14 + capnpc v0.10 (Cap'n Proto,
#          optional), glob v0.3 (file glob matching,
#          optional), serde + serde_json (GELF, JSON
#          encoding, optional), may (stackful
#          coroutines, optional).
# License: ISC (per Cargo.toml; README references
#          BSD-2 but Cargo.toml is authoritative)
# Status:  883+ stars on awslabs/flowgger; active
#          development (latest commit 2026-05-19);
#          stable v0.3.x release line; migrated
#          from chrono to time crate in v0.3.0
#          (2022-03-14) for RUSTSEC-2020-0071
#          compliance.
