#
# Axis 45 itself: Redis Client / In-Memory Key-Value
# Store Integration (libraries that wrap the Redis
# RESP protocol + provide idiomatic command APIs
# for the host language — as distinct from Axis 44
# Docker Client which wraps Docker Engine API, or
# generic process-spawning wrappers around the
# `redis-cli` binary).
#
# Pattern: R768 124th language (HVML/PurC) closes
# the prior 3+1 cycle → R769 Rust=100 LANDMARK
# (flowgger/redis-rs → Axis 45 OPENS THIS) is the
# first leader bump in the new cycle.  Pending:
# R770 Go=100 LANDMARK with a redis/go-redis user;
# R771 TS-Node=100 LANDMARK with a node-redis or
# ioredis user; R772 125th language.
#
# WHY redis-rs IS A DISTINCTIVE AXIS-45 OPENER:
#
#   redis-rs/redis by Armin Ronacher (also author
#   of Flask, Jinja2, Sentry's Python SDK,
#   minijinja, Click, Werkzeug, and many other
#   foundational Python + Rust libraries) is the
#   canonical Rust Redis client.  Distinguishing
#   characteristics:
#     1. SYNC + ASYNC APIs — supports both
#        synchronous (blocking) and asynchronous
#        (tokio + async-std) modes from the same
#        client codebase via feature flags.
#        Flowgger uses the sync API for its single-
#        threaded input pipeline
#     2. RESP2 + RESP3 PROTOCOLS — supports both
#        the original Redis Serialization Protocol
#        (RESP2; default through Redis 6) and the
#        newer RESP3 (Redis 6+) with push messages,
#        attribute records, and richer types
#     3. STREAMING APIs — supports Redis Streams
#        (`XADD` / `XREAD` / `XLEN` / `XACK`) +
#        Pub/Sub subscription with iterator-based
#        consumption
#     4. CLUSTER SUPPORT — first-class Redis Cluster
#        client via the `cluster` feature; handles
#        slot routing + automatic failover + MOVED/
#        ASK redirect responses transparently
#     5. CONNECTION POOLING — built-in connection
#        pool via the deadpool-redis sibling crate;
#        suitable for high-concurrency server
#        applications
#     6. COMMAND TRAIT EXTENSIBILITY — users can
#        define custom Redis commands by
#        implementing the Commands trait; supports
#        modules like RedisJSON, RedisSearch,
#        RedisTimeSeries without modifying the core
#        crate
#     7. ~3,800+ STARS ON redis-rs/redis
#     8. ECOSYSTEM-DOMINANT — used by flowgger
#        (this completion), almost every Rust web
#        framework's session store, sidekiq-rs,
#        cargo-redis, queue-rs, fred (sibling
#        higher-level client), and effectively
#        every Rust application that interacts
#        with Redis
#
# Maintained by Armin Ronacher (@mitsuhiko) +
# contributors at redis-rs/redis.  License: BSD-3-
# Clause.
